No. I want to speak to the president.

373
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:54,540
急事吗
Is it urgent?

374
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:57,150
我想跟他谈《美国就业法案》的事
I want to talk to him about the America Works program.

375
00:23:57,260 --> 00:23:58,270
那就不是急事喽
So nothing urgent.

376
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:00,300
对  不紧急
It's not an emergency, no.

377
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:02,150
因为这电话是仅供紧急情况
'Cause that's what this phone is for.

378
00:24:04,730 --> 00:24:06,290
你能转达下我的请求吗
Will you pass on my message?

379
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:33,510
你来迟了
You're late.

380
00:25:33,510 --> 00:25:35,150
我换了三辆出租车
I switched cabs three times.

381
00:25:36,050 --> 00:25:38,380
-你被人跟踪了吗  -不想抱侥幸心理
- Were you being followed? - Didn't want to take chances.

382
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,940
你知道我叫你来做什么
You know why I asked you here.

383
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:44,290
我不知道她在哪
I don't know where she is.

384
00:25:44,290 --> 00:25:45,520
那你就给我找到
Then you need to find out.

385
00:25:45,520 --> 00:25:47,350
我查了她的社保号  名字
I ran her social, her name,

386
00:25:47,490 --> 00:25:49,140
警方记录  税务记录  都查了
police records, taxes, everything.

387
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:51,760
她说不定被哪个嫖客丢在阴沟里了
She could be tossed in a ditch by a john for all I know.

388
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:54,420
-你在联调局工作  -有我什么好处
- You work at the FBI. - What do I get in return?

389
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:56,160
我的保护  如你所说
My protection, like you asked.

390
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:59,230
我以为你真有什么  货真价实的东西
I thought you had something to offer. Something real.

391
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:00,010
钱吗
Like money?

392
00:26:00,020 --> 00:26:01,230
比如帮我脱离联调局
Like getting me out of the Bureau.

393
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:03,320
你实现这一点  我或许能帮你
You make that happen, maybe I can help you.

394
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:07,340
说好的条件是撤销对你的指控
That was a condition, for your charges being dropped.

395
00:26:10,820 --> 00:26:12,420
瞧  你现在没人脉了
See, you don't still know people.

396
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:15,730
我就不该来
I shouldn't have even come here.

397
00:26:15,730 --> 00:26:17,590
我是你唯一的安全保障
I am your only safety net.

398
00:26:17,660 --> 00:26:19,670
你以为我会交出那些美国电话电报公司的记录
You think I would have turned over all the AT&T records

399
00:26:19,670 --> 00:26:21,630
而不给谁留个备份吗
without leaving a backup with somebody?

400
00:26:21,770 --> 00:26:24,970
我不会为了无用功报销我的免牢金牌
I'm not gonna blow my get-out-of-jail card on a wild goose chase.

401
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,090
有人起疑吗
Does anyone suspect anything?

402
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:30,740
联调局那边
At the Bureau?

403
00:26:32,890 --> 00:26:34,900
没人知道她
Nobody has a clue about her.

404
00:26:34,980 --> 00:26:36,830
如果能让你安心的话
If that gives you any peace of mind.

405
00:26:55,090 --> 00:26:56,170
道格
Doug?

406
00:26:56,180 --> 00:26:57,460
告诉他是急事
Tell him it's urgent.

407
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,370
我们希望能安排在五月
We're aiming for sometime in May.

408
00:27:00,370 --> 00:27:02,870
我们一跟俄国代表团敲定日期
As soon as we agree on a date with the Russian delegation,

409
00:27:02,870 --> 00:27:05,910
就马上告诉你  格雷格
you will be the first to know. Uh, Greg.

410
00:27:05,910 --> 00:27:07,630
与佩特罗夫在华盛顿的峰会
The Summit with Petrov here in Washington,

411
00:27:07,630 --> 00:27:09,450
会谈重点将是什么
what'll be the focus of the talks?

412
00:27:09,460 --> 00:27:11,470
对中东采取的双边政策
A bilateral approach to the Middle East.

413
00:27:11,470 --> 00:27:14,030
你也知道  以色列军队不撤离约旦河谷
As you know, the Palestinians have refused to negotiate

414
00:27:14,030 --> 00:27:16,120
巴勒斯坦就拒绝谈判
until Israeli troops leave the Jordan Valley.

415
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:18,660
我们希望与佩特罗夫总统商议此事
We hope to address this with President Petrov

416
00:27:18,660 --> 00:27:21,280
也好继续谈很多其他问题
so that we can move on to a whole host of other issues.

417
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:22,120
萨拉
Sara.

418
00:27:22,130 --> 00:27:25,260
那么这项政策的商议不包含以色列和巴勒斯坦
So this bilateral approach doesn't include Israel and Palestine.

419
00:27:25,260 --> 00:27:27,700
国务院在向所有相关方做简报
The State Department is briefing all interested parties.

420
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:29,900
峰会只是第一步  艾拉
The summit's really just a first step. Ayla.

421
00:27:29,900 --> 00:27:32,400
我想就《美国就业法案》提问
I'd like to change course to the America Works program.

422
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,200
请问
Please.

423
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,400
我采访了多位总统政策顾问
I've spoken to a number of the president's policy advisors,

424
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:37,900
他们说经济团队在这项就业计划
who say there's been a lot of disagreement on the economic team

425
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:41,470
该采取何种形式方面有很多分歧
as to exactly what form this jobs package should take.

426
00:27:41,470 --> 00:27:43,270
-哪些顾问  -想得美
- Which advisors? - Nice try.

427
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:47,390
我要说明  这并不仅仅是一项就业计划
To be clear, this is far more than just a jobs package.

428
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:48,780
是一项全面的计划
It is a comprehensive plan,

429
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:52,410
其目的是两年内实现全面就业
which aims at full employment within two years.

430
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:54,820
就此而言  还有很多细节问题有待解决
So as such, there are a lot of details to be worked out.

431
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:56,480
所以你的消息来源不准确
So your sources are inaccurate.

432
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,770
并非是什么分歧
It's not so much a disagreement

433
00:27:58,770 --> 00:28:01,590
而是就计划细节进行辩论  杰西
as it is debating the finer points of the plan. Jess.

434
00:28:01,590 --> 00:28:04,040
我想再追问一句  都有些什么细节问题
Just to follow up. What are some of the finer points?

435
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:05,320
甚至是计划大致是如何
Or the broad strokes, even.

436
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:07,220
白宫没有任何人透露任何信息
No one from the White House has said anything.

437
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:10,130
等我们能拿出计划  我们就会拿出来
When we have a plan to present, we will present it.

438
00:28:10,540 --> 00:28:11,550
杰西
Jess?

439
00:28:11,580 --> 00:28:13,070
《美国就业法案》是否是
Is America Works a reaction

440
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:15,260
针对总统低支持率的举措
to the president's low approval ratings?

441
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:17,990
为给竞选造势  而向民众展现政绩
An effort to offer some sign of progress ramping up to the elections?

442
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,740
我们从第一天就开始准备这项法案了
We've been working on this plan since day one.

443
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:21,280
这与支持率毫无关系
It has nothing to do with the approval ratings.

444
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:24,960
但至于选举  今天该谁问了
But as for the election... uh, whose turn is it to ask today?

445
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:28,310
-马克  -总统会参加2016年竞选吗
- Mark? - Is the president running in 2016?

446
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:31,600
今天  重点是好好执政  但是...
Today, the priority is good government, but...

447
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:34,350
明天接着问吧
Ask me again tomorrow.

448
00:28:34,350 --> 00:28:35,940
谢谢大家
Thank you, everyone.

449
00:28:37,470 --> 00:28:38,900
10点钟有个空窗
We've got a window at ten.

450
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,170
我这就打给他
I'll call him now.

451
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,100
请坐
Please, sit down.

452
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:48,960
约翰  萨曼莎
John. Samantha.

453
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:51,880
你们跟记者说我们这屋里出现的分歧了吗
You spoke to a journalist about disagreements in this room?

454
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:54,120
再发生一次  你们就走人吧
If that happens again, you're off the team.

455
00:28:54,390 --> 00:28:56,420
说到这屋里出现的分歧
And speaking of the disagreements in this room,

456
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:57,760
我们现在出现了更大的分歧
we now have an even bigger one,

457
00:28:57,760 --> 00:29:01,690
雷米给我看了你们目前的成果
because Remy has shown me your work so far and...

458
00:29:02,810 --> 00:29:04,090
无力
it's toothless.

459
00:29:04,980 --> 00:29:06,640
我三个月前站在这间屋子里
I stood in this room three months ago

460
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:08,620
给你们下达了明确的指令
and gave you all very clear direction.

461
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:11,550
社会保险  医疗保险  医疗补助
Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid,

462
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:14,400
所有这些在吸干国库的福利项目
every entitlement program that is sucking us dry,

463
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,360
全都放在桌上
I want it all on the table.

464
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,030
这还远远不够
And this doesn't go nearly far enough.

465
00:29:18,030 --> 00:29:20,650
所以我们显然是得回到一些基本问题上了
So we obviously have to get back to some basics.

466
00:29:20,650 --> 00:29:23,540
回顾一些摆在我们面前的事实
Remind ourselves of some of the facts that are before us--

467
00:29:23,540 --> 00:29:25,990
-先生  我能...  -不不不
- Sir, if I may-- - No, no, no, no.

468
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:30,780
我先说  然后你再说  保罗
I will speak first, and then you will speak, Paul.

469
00:29:34,420 --> 00:29:37,080
这是国民一年平均从福利项目
This is what the average senior citizen gets,

470
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:38,680
得到的数额
one year from entitlements,

471
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:41,370
不管是清洁工  还是对冲基金经理
whether they were a janitor or they ran a hedge fund.

472
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:45,300
这笔钱  就是一份
That-- This money is a job

473
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,100
我们本可给一位单身母亲
we could be giving to a single mother

474
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:48,530
或应届毕业生的工作
or a student just out of school.

475
00:29:48,530 --> 00:29:49,850
现在呢
Now, at the moment,

476
00:29:50,150 --> 00:29:54,580
每一元的税中有44美分流向了这些项目
44 cents of every tax dollar goes to pay for these programs.

477
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:57,800
到2030年  就将超过一半  62美分
By 2030, it'll be over half, 62 cents.

478
00:29:57,800 --> 00:30:00,580
福利项目在让国家破产
Entitlements are bankrupting us.

479
00:30:00,580 --> 00:30:03,170
我让雷米进行了一项民调
Now, I had Remy conduct a little poll.

480
00:30:03,170 --> 00:30:05,330
提出陈述为  "做对国家有益的事
Statement posed was: "Doing what's best for my country

481
00:30:05,330 --> 00:30:07,260
等于做我不喜欢的事"
means doing some things that I don't like."

482
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:10,030
74%的人认同这一陈述
Seventy-four percent agreed with this statement.

483
00:30:10,330 --> 00:30:13,560
74%  这说明什么
Seventy-four percent. Now, what does that tell us?

484
00:30:13,780 --> 00:30:17,550
我们必须做人们不会喜欢的事
We have to do the things that people won't like.

485
00:30:17,550 --> 00:30:18,810
即便我们做了
And even when we do,

486
00:30:18,810 --> 00:30:20,850
也会有四分之三的人支持我们
three out of four of them will go along with us.

487
00:30:20,850 --> 00:30:24,450
为什么  因为我们能保证就业
And why? Because we're promising jobs.

488
00:30:24,450 --> 00:30:27,290
再说一遍  我们要在哪三个领域
And again, where are the three areas

489
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:29,880
创造就业呢
that we're gonna be creating these jobs from?

490
00:30:30,740 --> 00:30:33,410
州和联邦基础建设项目
Infrastructure at the state and federal level.

491
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:35,580
扩大军队
Increasing the size of the military,

492
00:30:35,580 --> 00:30:37,910
并与私营部门合作
and working with our friends in the private sector to start--

493
00:30:37,910 --> 00:30:40,840
抱歉  先生  我必须打断
I'm sorry, sir, but I have to interrupt.

494
00:30:40,930 --> 00:30:43,920
你要削减或砍掉的项目
The programs that you want to scale back or dismantle

495
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:46,510
是美国梦的基石啊
are the bedrock of the American dream.

496
00:30:46,510 --> 00:30:48,160
工作努力  交税
You work hard, you pay your taxes--

497
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:51,160
不  抱歉  那曾是美国梦的基石
No, I'm sorry, they were the bedrock of the American dream.

498
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:52,720
但现在不是了
But they're not anymore.

499
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,850
尤其是对那失业的一千万人来说
Certainly not for the ten million people who are out of work.

500
00:30:55,850 --> 00:30:59,400
但从实际角度出发  数千特殊利益群体
But practically speaking, a thousand special interests,

501
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,790
工会  两党都有反对声音
organized labor, opposition in both parties.

502
00:31:01,790 --> 00:31:04,750
我们可以就你的提议折中一下...
Now, we can do a version of what you're proposing--

503
00:31:04,750 --> 00:31:07,250
我不要折中
I don't want a version.

504
00:31:07,860 --> 00:31:10,100
我要远大愿景
I want a vision.

505
00:31:10,830 --> 00:31:14,660
作为团队领袖  我认为我可以代表所有人说
As head of this team, and I think I speak for everyone,

506
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:18,120
-我们已经...  -作为总统
- we have done-- - Speaking as the president,

507
00:31:18,170 --> 00:31:21,000
我选择了这支团队  你们为我工作
who chose this team and for whom it works,

508
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,630
我要拿到五千亿美元
I want five hundred billion dollars

509
00:31:23,630 --> 00:31:25,870
给一千万民众工作
to put ten million people to work.

510
00:31:25,870 --> 00:31:27,840
我不管这多让人肉疼
I don't care how much it hurts.

511
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:30,330
我不管这有多具争议性
I don't care how controversial it is.

512
00:31:30,330 --> 00:31:33,000
你们的职责  就是找出办法
Your job is to find a way.

513
00:31:33,260 --> 00:31:37,170
说服国会和美国人民是我的工作
It's my job to convince Congress and the American people.

514
00:31:37,170 --> 00:31:42,210
你们的工作不是向我推销你们的妥协方案
Your job is not to sell me on your version of my program.

515
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,820
大家都清楚自己该做什么了吗
Now, are we all clear on what our jobs are?

516
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,870
很好  因为我要在30天内
Good, because I want to present this proposal

517
00:31:47,870 --> 00:31:50,000
向领导层呈递这份提议
to leadership in 30 days.

518
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:52,000
-我们实现这个目标吧  -保罗
- Let's make it happen. - Paul?

519
00:31:57,620 --> 00:32:00,080
-我们不再需要你了  -什么
- Your services are no longer needed. - Excuse me?

520
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,980
别声张  保持和气
Let's keep it quiet, let's keep it cordial.

521
00:32:02,690 --> 00:32:05,220
-多谢你的辛劳  -我去收拾东西
- Thanks for all your work. - I'll get my things.

522
00:32:05,220 --> 00:32:06,580
我会叫人给你送到大厅的
I'll have them sent down to you in the lobby.

523
00:32:41,270 --> 00:32:42,120
喂
Hello?

524
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:45,330
好的  马上就来
Yeah. I'm on my way.

525
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:24,450
天啊
God!

526
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:22,760
天啊
God!

527
00:34:30,370 --> 00:34:32,840
请您稍等几分钟  请坐
It'll be a few minutes. Please, have a seat.

528
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:51,700
-你知道多久了  -两个月
- How long have you known? - Two months.

529
00:34:52,740 --> 00:34:55,360
我作为法官的能力尚未受到影响
It hasn't impaired my judgment on the bench.

530
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,330
而且目前只是早期
And it's early on.

531
00:34:56,330 --> 00:34:59,500
还要一段时间才会有一些明显的症状
We don't expect any real symptoms for quite some time.

532
00:35:00,410 --> 00:35:03,370
暂时我还不会穿着
I won't be wandering around the Supreme Court

533
00:35:03,370 --> 00:35:05,870
短裤在最高法院乱晃
in my boxer shorts anytime soon.

534
00:35:06,020 --> 00:35:11,050
但是我想现在就趁早退休  别到那一步
But I'd like to retire now, long before we get there.

535
00:35:11,210 --> 00:35:13,840
大法官  我非常感谢你能有勇气来
Well, Justice, I want to thank you for having the courage

536
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:16,010
告知我这个消息
to come and share this news with me.

537
00:35:16,010 --> 00:35:18,070
你确定诊断无误吗
Are you sure the diagnosis is correct?

538
00:35:18,070 --> 00:35:21,380
我的医生就是给副总统夫人看病的那位
My doctor's the same that treated the Vice President's wife.

539
00:35:21,390 --> 00:35:23,850
他是美国最厉害的老年痴呆专家
He's the foremost Alzheimer's specialist in America.

540
00:35:25,180 --> 00:35:27,300
是的  我任命唐纳德为副总统了
Yes, I made Donald my vice president.

541
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:30,130
与其让他在国会惹事  不如放在身边
I'd rather him be a pain in my ass here than over in Congress.

542
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:31,180
而且就算是共和党员
And even the Republicans

543
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:33,330
也不能拒绝刚刚经历丧妻之痛的人
couldn't refuse a man who just buried his wife.

544
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:35,320
玛乔莉走得这么快真是可怕
Terrible how quickly Marjory went.

545
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,300
我现在就告诉你
I'm telling you this now

546
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:39,560
这样你就有时间考虑一下人选
so you have time to think about candidates

547
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:42,030
然后我再宣布退休
before I announce my retirement.

548
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:45,430
-你能给我多长时间  -你需要多长时间
- How much time can you give me? - How much do you need?

549
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:47,850
我正要向国会提出《美国就业法案》
I'm about to introduce America Works to Congress.

550
00:35:47,850 --> 00:35:49,450
肯定不会轻松
It's sure to be an uphill battle.

551
00:35:49,450 --> 00:35:53,310
还是不要再加个最高法院法官提名来添乱了
And I'd prefer not to add a Supreme Court nomination to the mix.

552
00:35:53,430 --> 00:35:55,400
共和党肯定会拿这个当筹码
The Republicans will just use it as leverage.

553
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:58,810
我听到了一些风声  要拿福利开刀吗
I've heard rumblings. Entitlements on the chopping block?

554
00:35:58,810 --> 00:36:00,690
所以更需要你继续坐镇
All the more reason to keep you on the bench.

555
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:02,910
司法部肯定会提出异议
It's sure to be challenged in the Judiciary.

556
00:36:03,930 --> 00:36:08,610
总统先生  我想和我妻子
Mr. President, I want to spend as much time

557
00:36:08,610 --> 00:36:10,810
尽量多在一起
with my wife as possible

558
00:36:11,190 --> 00:36:14,330
趁着我这两年还清醒
in the good years that I have left.

559
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,760
玛乔莉确诊的时候  她也是这么想的
When Marjory was ill, she wanted the same thing.

560
00:36:18,460 --> 00:36:20,750
她离开了史密森尼学会  但是你知道吗
She left the Smithsonian, and you know what?

561
00:36:20,750 --> 00:36:24,330
她在家每一秒都很烦躁  因为不能做事了
She hated every second of being at home, of not being productive,

562
00:36:24,330 --> 00:36:26,220
不能从事自己热爱的事业
of not doing what she loved.

563
00:36:27,070 --> 00:36:30,340
她那段时间过得很艰难
It made her time with us much harder, and...

564
00:36:31,450 --> 00:36:33,840
也非常不开心
it made her deeply unhappy.

565
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:37,430
工作是最好的调剂  我真希望她当时没退休
Work is the best distraction. I wish she hadn't retired.

566
00:36:37,430 --> 00:36:41,480
而且  她头脑还清楚的时候
And, uh... before she lost her lucid thought,

567
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,220
她说她也很后悔
she said she regretted it, too.

568
00:36:43,340 --> 00:36:47,220
能不能再坚持六个月  最多一年
Can you give me six months? A year at the most? That's all.

569
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,620
让我在应付最高法院的争斗之前
Just enough time to get this program up and running

570
00:36:49,620 --> 00:36:51,830
能有时间让这个法案顺利开展
before I have to face a Supreme Court fight.

571
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,190
-我得考虑考虑  -当然
- I need to think it over. - Oh, of course.

572
00:36:57,190 --> 00:36:59,410
-和你夫人商量一下  -我送你出去
- Speak to your wife. - I'll walk you out.

573
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:07,810
-研究中心尽快给我落实  -说话算话
- I better get that research center. - Yes, a deal is a deal.

574
00:37:07,810 --> 00:37:10,110
上帝啊  唐纳德  咱们赶紧干活儿吧
Now, good God, Donald, let's get something done.

575
00:37:14,550 --> 00:37:16,400
现在你知道为什么唐纳德会同意了
Now you see why Donald said yes.

576
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,010
他虽恨我入骨
He may hate my guts,

577
00:37:18,700 --> 00:37:20,240
但是再没什么比家庭成员去世
but there's nothing like a death in the family

578
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:22,250
更能让人识时务了
to separate the wheat from the bullshit.

579
00:37:23,050 --> 00:37:23,760
让他进来吧
Send him in.

580
00:37:23,770 --> 00:37:24,580
是  先生
Yes, sir.

581
00:37:25,990 --> 00:37:27,580
总统可以见你了
The president is ready to see you now.

582
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:49,040
道格
Doug.

583
00:37:51,420 --> 00:37:52,390
总统先生
Mr. President.

584
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:58,010
医生告诉我你恢复得很好
The doctor told me your recovery is going very well.

585
00:37:58,060 --> 00:37:59,610
是啊  就是要用这个
Yeah. Well, there's this.

586
00:38:00,540 --> 00:38:02,170
别的地方都恢复如初
But everything else is as good as new.

587
00:38:02,450 --> 00:38:03,960
见到你真是太好了
It's great to see you.

588
00:38:04,020 --> 00:38:05,980
克莱尔和我担心得要死
Claire and I have been worried sick about you.

589
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:07,180
谢谢你们的礼物
Thank you for the gifts.

590
00:38:07,870 --> 00:38:08,820
也谢谢你们的照顾
For looking out for me.

591
00:38:08,820 --> 00:38:11,880
我没多少亲密的朋友  你是其中之一
I don't have that many close friends. I count you among them.

592
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:14,470
我很感激你这么说  先生
I appreciate your saying that, sir.

593
00:38:14,470 --> 00:38:16,620
别叫我先生  我们是老朋友了
Oh, drop the "Sir." We're old pals.

594
00:38:17,860 --> 00:38:18,740
嗯
Well...

595
00:38:20,090 --> 00:38:21,990
我才应该道歉
I'm the one who should apologize.

596
00:38:22,730 --> 00:38:26,080
你又给了我个机会  你相信我
You gave me another chance. You trusted me.

597
00:38:27,260 --> 00:38:29,340
这一切我一人承担
And what happened, I take responsibility for that.

598
00:38:29,340 --> 00:38:30,740
让你陷入那种处境
No, for putting you in that position.

599
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:32,240
别  没这必要
Stop. It's not necessary.

600
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:34,740
-我让你身陷危机  -没错  但我只在乎
- I endangered you just as-- - Yeah, but all I care about

601
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:37,740
你还活着  在逐渐恢复
is that you are alive and getting better.

602
00:38:37,750 --> 00:38:39,540
其它的都过去吧
Let the rest of it go.

603
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:44,120
-你知道我多忠心  -这不用你说
- You know how devoted I am. - You don't have to say it.

604
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:46,260
你一次又一次地证明了自己
You proved it time and time again.

605
00:38:46,260 --> 00:38:47,790
来  坐下
Now, come on, come on, sit down.

606
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,020
坐在这儿
Right here.

607
00:39:13,950 --> 00:39:16,160
当初有机会时我就该解决了她
I should've taken care of her when I had the chance.

608
00:39:19,550 --> 00:39:20,790
我还没找到她
I haven't found her yet.

609
00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:24,810
等我找到她  一定确保别人再找不到
But when I do, I'll make sure that no one else does.

610
00:39:25,710 --> 00:39:27,200
我向你保证  先生
You can count on that, sir.

611
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,160
你打算怎么办...
How is it, uh...?

612
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:33,300
我不告诉你可能比较好
Probably better if we don't talk about it.

613
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:34,940
嗯  是啊
Right, of course.

614
00:39:38,150 --> 00:39:40,220
他们说你要见我
Well, they told me you needed to see me.

615
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:46,080
先生  我知道这要求很过分
Well, sir, I... I know that it's a lot to ask,

616
00:39:46,490 --> 00:39:47,660
我给我们惹了这么大麻烦
and that I probably don't deserve it,

617
00:39:47,660 --> 00:39:49,450
我或许也不配
considering the mess I put us in.

618
00:39:49,870 --> 00:39:51,770
你肯定也有顾虑
And I'm sure you have your doubts.

619
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:54,950
我知道我不能明目张胆  但...
I realize it couldn't be anything too visible, but...

620
00:39:55,550 --> 00:39:57,540
我一直在跟进《美国就业法案》的报道
I've been following everything with America Works.

621
00:39:57,820 --> 00:39:59,180
这扯哪去了
Well, that's a ways off.

622
00:39:59,180 --> 00:40:00,700
我觉得我能帮上忙
But I was thinking that I could help.

623
00:40:01,590 --> 00:40:04,660
游说委员会领导层应该有明确目标
There should be a targeted plan for lobbying committee leadership.

624
00:40:04,800 --> 00:40:06,450
我能配合政治团队
And I can work with the political team,

625
00:40:06,450 --> 00:40:09,010
协调国会立法主任和幕僚长
coordinate with House leg directors, chiefs of staff--

626
00:40:09,010 --> 00:40:12,580
我昨天去了加夫尼给我父亲扫墓
I was in Gaffney yesterday, visiting my father's grave.

627
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:15,180
他从不好好照顾自己
He never took care of himself.

628
00:40:15,300 --> 00:40:19,870
不顾自己心脏有病  最终付出代价
He ignored his heart problems and... he paid the price.

629
00:40:22,110 --> 00:40:24,730
你得尊重自己终有一死的命运  道格
You have to respect your own mortality, Doug.

630
00:40:24,740 --> 00:40:27,040
我不想给你收尸
I don't want to be standing over your grave.

631
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:28,210
告诉你...
Now, look...

632
00:40:28,990 --> 00:40:33,610
我保证你在这里会有一席之地
There is a place for you here, I promise.

633
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:36,060
但心急吃不了热豆腐
But we have to go about this slowly.

634
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:38,770
我在家工作  只跟你和雷米直接接触
I'll work from home. Only direct contact with you or Remy.

635
00:40:38,780 --> 00:40:40,440
要知道你帮我的最好办法
You know the way that you can help me the best

636
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,380
就是好好恢复身体
is to do exactly what you're doing right now,

637
00:40:42,380 --> 00:40:44,230
不要分心
focusing on your recovery.

638
00:40:44,350 --> 00:40:45,710
如果我操之过急
I would never forgive myself

639
00:40:45,710 --> 00:40:48,890
让你压力太大  我绝不会原谅自己
if I put too much on your plate too soon.

640
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:53,670
没错
You're right.

641
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:56,880
抱歉
I'm sorry.

642
00:41:04,580 --> 00:41:05,340
谢谢
Thank you.

643
00:41:05,340 --> 00:41:06,880
抱歉  我得走了
I'm sorry, I have to go.

644
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:10,400
但我说的都是真心话
But look, I meant what I said.

645
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,740
等你准备好了再说
When you are truly ready.

646
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:14,180
是  先生
Yes, sir.

647
00:41:15,100 --> 00:41:16,520
你想待多久待多久
Stay as long as you like.

648
00:41:35,510 --> 00:41:37,970
三小时前  我们定位到
Three hours ago, we pinpointed him here,

649
00:41:37,970 --> 00:41:39,920
他在也门的夏卜瓦省
in the Shabwa region of Yemen.

650
00:41:40,690 --> 00:41:41,610
配合方面呢
Cooperation?

651
00:41:41,610 --> 00:41:43,990
我几分钟前和外交部长谈过
I spoke to the foreign minister a few minutes ago.

652
00:41:43,990 --> 00:41:46,260
-有多少平民  -二十几个  不明身份
- Civilians? - Two dozen, non-IDs.

653
00:41:46,260 --> 00:41:47,440
太多了
That's too many.

654
00:41:47,850 --> 00:41:50,710
我们担心他可能随时离开
Our concern is that he could be on the move at any moment.

655
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:52,500
先生  鉴于佩特罗夫要来华盛顿...
Sir, with Petrov coming to Washington--

656
00:41:52,500 --> 00:41:55,130
我们花了两年才找到阿卜杜拉
It's taken us two years to track Abdullah down.

657
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:58,200
不能为了峰会就放弃一切机会
We can't ignore every opportunity between now and the summit.

658
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:00,970
你们看到村子情况了吗
Do you have eyes on the village?

659
00:42:00,970 --> 00:42:01,810
是的  先生
Yes, sir.

660
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:04,730
他就在这栋房子里
He's in this building here.

661
00:42:04,750 --> 00:42:07,130
50米内不留活口
Kill zone is anyone within 50 meters.

662
00:42:09,770 --> 00:42:11,600
如果没有平民伤亡就能除掉他
If we take him out with no civilian casualties,

663
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:12,820
我就同意这次袭击
I'll authorize the strike.

664
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:14,440
先生  恕我冒昧  我真心认为
Sir, if I may, I really think--

665
00:42:14,450 --> 00:42:17,810
还有不到两个月佩特罗夫总统就将来访华盛顿
President Petrov is coming to Washington in less than two months.

666
00:42:17,810 --> 00:42:21,480
我们整个中东政策都靠这次峰会
Our entire Middle East policy hinges on that meeting.

667
00:42:21,510 --> 00:42:24,920
如果可能  我们不想给穆斯林社会任何
We don't want to give the Muslim community any viable reasons

668
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:27,230
阻挠进程的借口
to obstruct things if we can avoid it.

669
00:42:27,810 --> 00:42:29,860
想办法不杀死平民就除掉他
So find a way to do this without killing civilians.

670
00:42:29,860 --> 00:42:31,180
非常感谢各位
Thank you all very much.

671
00:42:31,420 --> 00:42:34,730
能单独谈会儿吗  是克莱尔的事
May I have a moment? It's about Claire.

672
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,760
如果你丈夫提名你  我不会手下留情的
If your husband nominates you, I can't pull any punches.

673
00:42:38,570 --> 00:42:41,050
没经验  任人唯亲
Lack of experience. Nepotism.

674
00:42:41,050 --> 00:42:42,060
没错
That's right.

675
00:42:42,700 --> 00:42:44,470
你觉得我太业余
And you think I'm a dilettante.

676
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:47,430
不  但很多人会这么认为
No. But plenty of people will.

677
00:42:47,970 --> 00:42:50,520
打从弗兰西斯一就职我就在准备了
I've been preparing since Francis took office.

678
00:42:50,570 --> 00:42:53,580
经验的缺乏我会用职业道德补上
What I lack in experience I'll make up for in work ethic.

679
00:42:54,020 --> 00:42:55,720
为什么要当联合国大使
Why Ambassador to the UN?

680
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:57,800
你作为第一夫人有更大的影响力
You wield far more influence as the First Lady.

681
00:42:57,800 --> 00:43:00,940
那和切实地去做贡献不一样
That's not the same as contributing in a concrete way.

682
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,350
如果我们投票否决了你
If we vote down your confirmation,

683
00:43:03,410 --> 00:43:07,560
你能接受在公众面前丢面子吗
are you comfortable with that sort of public embarrassment?

684
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:09,570
我知道有这风险
I know that's a risk.

685
00:43:11,790 --> 00:43:15,730
-你2016年会竞选吧  -无可奉告
- You're running in 2016, right? - No comment.

686
00:43:15,730 --> 00:43:17,460
弗兰西斯和我都惊讶于
Francis and I are impressed

687
00:43:17,830 --> 00:43:20,700
共和党人如此支持你
by how the Republicans are consolidating around you.

688
00:43:21,170 --> 00:43:22,260
你会是一个优秀的候选人
You'll make a good candidate.

689
00:43:22,260 --> 00:43:24,800
但不能和总统夫人勾结
Not by linking arms with the president's wife.

690
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:29,350
如果我搞砸了  这会是有力的竞选广告
If I'm a disaster, it makes for a good campaign ad.

691
00:43:29,570 --> 00:43:32,110
如果我做得好  那你更是无可指摘
If I do a good job, nobody can fault you.

692
00:43:32,110 --> 00:43:35,140
无论如何这都不会影响你2016的竞选
Either way, it doesn't hurt your chances in 2016.

693
00:43:37,350 --> 00:43:41,240
我很感激你在公布消息前先来找我
Well, I appreciate you coming by before going public.

694
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:44,300
很有风度也很周到
It is classy, and thoughtful.

695
00:43:45,290 --> 00:43:46,900
我不会故意阻碍你的
I won't actively block you.

696
00:43:47,410 --> 00:43:49,610
剩下就靠你自己努力了
The rest is on your shoulders.

697
00:43:50,710 --> 00:43:52,000
谢谢  参议员
Thank you, Senator.

698
00:43:53,260 --> 00:43:56,220
告诉总统我这么做是出于对你的敬意
Tell the president I'm doing this out of respect to you.

699
00:43:57,160 --> 00:43:59,440
我在普选上打败弗兰克前  他都会在我黑名单上
Frank's still on my shit list till I beat him in the general.

700
00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:00,540
好的
I will.

701
00:44:02,210 --> 00:44:03,630
你怎么不立刻过来
Why didn't you come right away?

702
00:44:04,410 --> 00:44:06,220
我有个会面不能错过
I had a meeting I couldn't miss.

703
00:44:06,380 --> 00:44:07,860
该死的华盛顿
Fucking Washington.

704
00:44:08,230 --> 00:44:10,510
-会有些疼  -我知道
- This is gonna hurt. - I know.

705
00:44:15,290 --> 00:44:17,530
这是扑热息痛  能止痛
Here's some Percocet. It'll help with the pain.

706
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:20,830
我给你开个30天的处方
I'll write you a 30-day prescription.

707
00:44:20,830 --> 00:44:21,950
我不能
I can't.

708
00:44:22,330 --> 00:44:24,450
-我不能...  -什么
- I'm not supposed to-- - What was that?

709
00:44:27,270 --> 00:44:28,450
没事
Nothing.

710
00:44:37,560 --> 00:44:39,150
好了  你可以走了
All right. You're good to go.

711
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:22,450
-和门多萨谈得如何  -我觉得还不错
- How did it go with Mendoza? - Well, I think.

712
00:45:22,450 --> 00:45:23,680
他会支持你吗
He'll support you?

713
00:45:24,050 --> 00:45:26,070
他不会公开反对
He won't openly fight it.

714
00:45:26,640 --> 00:45:28,920
那可以一大进步
Well, that is a big step forward.

715
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:31,710
-道格说了什么  -没什么新消息
- How did it go with Doug? - No real news.

716
00:45:34,330 --> 00:45:36,390
你今晚还要在这里睡吗
Hey, are you in here again tonight?

717
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:39,320
我感冒还没好  不想传染给你
I'm still getting over this cold. I don't want to get you sick.

718
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:41,120
好吧  别做事做得太晚了
Well, don't stay up with all that too late.

719
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:42,170
弗兰西斯
Francis?

720
00:45:43,490 --> 00:45:45,470
我们什么时候公布提名
When do we announce the nomination?

721
00:45:50,510 --> 00:45:52,760
听着  我今晚本来不想谈这事
Listen, I wasn't gonna bring this up tonight,

722
00:45:52,760 --> 00:45:55,390
可你得知道国务院那边
but you should know that there are some serious doubts

723
00:45:55,390 --> 00:45:57,350
有很多疑虑
from people at the State Department.

724
00:45:57,610 --> 00:45:59,090
你是说凯茜
You mean Cathy.

725
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:01,430
还有她的一些手下
And some on her staff.

726
00:46:03,710 --> 00:46:04,710
什么样的疑虑
Like what?

727
00:46:04,710 --> 00:46:08,640
就是"能力不足""身兼两职"之类的
Well, in over your head, wearing two hats, the obvious things.

728
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:11,730
你是不是不想这么做了才这么说
And are you saying this because you don't want to move forward?

729
00:46:11,730 --> 00:46:14,850
当然不是  我告诉你  是希望你完全明白
Not at all. I'm sharing with you so you fully understand

730
00:46:14,850 --> 00:46:16,240
你要面对的情况
what you're getting into.

731
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:17,770
我明白
And I do.

732
00:46:23,780 --> 00:46:25,570
或许我们不该着急
Maybe we shouldn't rush this.

733
00:46:27,810 --> 00:46:30,870
-你现在也有疑虑了  -我可没这么说
- You're having doubts now, too. - I didn't say that.

734
00:46:30,870 --> 00:46:32,670
只是你该多考虑考虑这么做
Only you should put more thought into whether

735
00:46:32,670 --> 00:46:35,280
是否对你合适  就是这样
this is the right move for you. That's all.

736
00:46:37,210 --> 00:46:38,530
晚安  弗兰西斯
Good night, Francis.

737
00:46:40,210 --> 00:46:41,430
早日康复
Feel better.

738
00:47:53,580 --> 00:47:54,710
弗兰西斯
Francis.

739
00:47:56,610 --> 00:47:59,490
我想你这周宣布提名的消息
I want you to announce the nomination this week.

740
00:47:59,760 --> 00:48:02,670
我不想等了  没有什么好时机
I don't want to wait. The timing will never be good.

741
00:48:02,670 --> 00:48:03,810
我明明能积攒实战经验
And I don't want to waste time

742
00:48:03,810 --> 00:48:06,300
何必要浪费时间呢
when I can be getting real experience under my belt.

743
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:09,230
定个日子举办新闻发布会吧
So set a date, hold a press conference, and let's do it.

744
00:48:17,660 --> 00:48:18,790
克莱尔
Claire!

745
00:48:19,570 --> 00:48:23,350
我提到凯茜并不是说我认为
I was not trying to suggest that you not be the ambassador

746
00:48:23,350 --> 00:48:24,680
你不该当大使  我只是...
when I brought up Cathy. I was just--

747
00:48:24,690 --> 00:48:26,290
我们早说好了
We made a deal,

748
00:48:26,290 --> 00:48:28,130
现在你却要食言了
and now you're trying to back away from it.

749
00:48:28,130 --> 00:48:30,050
-不是这样的  -那你就会告诉凯茜
- That is not true. - Then you would've told Cathy

750
00:48:30,050 --> 00:48:32,170
事情就是这样  让她接受
it's happening to make her peace with that.

751
00:48:32,510 --> 00:48:35,060
-没那么简单  -就是那么简单
- It's not that simple. - Yes, it is.

752
00:48:35,060 --> 00:48:39,070
-你是总统  -我不能控制国会
- You're the president. - I can't control Congress.

753
00:48:39,070 --> 00:48:41,640
我想启动两项重要项目
I'm trying to get two major initiatives off the ground

754
00:48:41,640 --> 00:48:43,890
我的每一步行动都将产生影响
and every move I make will have an effect.

755
00:48:43,980 --> 00:48:47,420
我们早在走进白宫之前就已经说定了
We agreed to this before we ever stepped foot in this house.

756
00:48:47,420 --> 00:48:50,340
-我知道我们说定了  -如果我没有
- I know what we agreed to. - How am I supposed to run for office

757
00:48:50,340 --> 00:48:53,280
令人信服的资历  日后我怎么竞选总统
at some point if I don't have a legitimate track record?

758
00:48:53,280 --> 00:48:56,610
我们必须撑过接下来这18个月
We have to survive the next 18 months,

759
00:48:56,610 --> 00:49:00,150
取得点成绩  再说后面的事
accomplish something, and then look ahead.

760
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:04,350
弗兰西斯  我们还是现实一点
Francis, let's be realistic.

761
00:49:05,850 --> 00:49:08,260
你能否当选总统完全是没准的事
There's no guarantee you'll get elected.

762
00:49:08,390 --> 00:49:10,730
如果你落选  我得有所准备
I need to be prepared if you don't.

763
00:49:10,730 --> 00:49:12,500
你对我还真是有信心啊
You have that much faith in me, do you?

764
00:49:12,500 --> 00:49:14,420
看来比你对我的信心要大
More faith than you have in me, it seems.

765
00:49:14,420 --> 00:49:16,520
我相信你胜过任何人  克莱尔
I believe in you more than anyone, Claire.

766
00:49:16,520 --> 00:49:18,090
那表现出来  提名我
Then show it. Nominate me.

767
00:49:18,090 --> 00:49:19,240
别让我再费口舌说服你
I shouldn't have to convince you.

768
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:20,990
不是说不说服的事
It's not about convincing.

769
00:49:20,990 --> 00:49:24,050
而是我们得看清当下的政治气候
It's about being honest about the political climate

770
00:49:24,050 --> 00:49:26,890
-我们现在的处境  -我快要年过半百了
- that we find ourselves-- - I'm almost 50 years old.

771
00:49:27,430 --> 00:49:29,890
几十年来我一直当你的贤内助
I've been in the passenger seat for decades.

772
00:49:29,890 --> 00:49:31,700
也该让我自主一回了
It's time for me to get behind the wheel.

773
00:49:31,700 --> 00:49:35,320
必须现在就开始着手  赶在大选之前
That needs to start now. Before the election.

774
00:49:35,660 --> 00:49:37,450
因为谁知道那时会发生什么
Because who knows what will happen?

775
00:49:37,710 --> 00:49:38,950
万一你输了呢
What if you lose?

776
00:49:41,870 --> 00:49:45,520
我不会只当个填座总统的  克莱尔
I will not be a placeholder president, Claire.

777
00:49:47,120 --> 00:49:52,300
我一定会赢  我会名垂青史
I will win. And I will leave a legacy.

778
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:54,150
你是说我们会名垂青史
You mean we will.

779
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:55,220
打扰了  先生
Excuse me, sir.

780
00:49:55,220 --> 00:49:57,890
国防部长来电  他说有要事
The Secretary of Defense is on the line. He says it's urgent.

781
00:50:02,170 --> 00:50:03,190
什么事
Yes?

782
00:50:05,190 --> 00:50:06,280
好的
Okay.

783
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,080
我这就去
I'm coming.

784
00:50:08,520 --> 00:50:09,930
等我到了再开始
Not until I get there.

785
00:50:10,450 --> 00:50:12,040
-我马上下去  -好的  先生
- I'll be right down. - Yes, sir.

786
00:50:18,090 --> 00:50:20,300
穿好衣服  我有东西要给你看
Get dressed. I want you to see something.

787
00:51:17,540 --> 00:51:18,310
进来
Come in.

788
00:51:32,060 --> 00:51:33,400
-给  -多谢
- Here. - Thank you.

789
00:51:36,370 --> 00:51:37,440
那好
Okay, great.

790
00:51:39,240 --> 00:51:40,380
去脱吧
Get undressed.

791
00:52:38,660 --> 00:52:40,010
这是怎么回事
How did this happen?

792
00:52:40,670 --> 00:52:41,830
不重要
Doesn't matter.

793
00:52:53,670 --> 00:52:54,810
我来帮你
Let me help you.

794
00:53:05,290 --> 00:53:07,130
让我来
I'll... I'll do it.

795
00:53:22,070 --> 00:53:23,390
我会小心的
I'll be gentle.

796
00:53:28,890 --> 00:53:30,130
不用小心
Don't be gentle.

797
00:53:31,640 --> 00:53:32,750
像这样吗
Like that?

798
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:35,190
没错
Yeah.

799
00:53:46,290 --> 00:53:48,390
-搞什么鬼  -是波本
- What the fuck? - It's bourbon.

800
00:53:48,520 --> 00:53:50,820
-我  -只是波本而已
- I-- - That's all. It's just bourbon.

801
00:53:51,780 --> 00:53:54,000
-拿着  -我真不想
- Take it. - I really don't want to.

802
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:55,660
不是用来注射的
Nothing's going through the skin.

803
00:53:56,660 --> 00:53:58,330
我只是想让你
I just want you to squirt it...

804
00:53:59,430 --> 00:54:00,610
把酒射进我嘴里
into my mouth.

805
00:54:02,150 --> 00:54:04,680
好吗  拜托了
Okay? Please.

806
00:54:16,010 --> 00:54:17,680
-那是目标吗  -是的  先生
- Is that our target? - Yes, sir.

807
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:21,280
总统先生  这次行动是高度机密
Mr. President, this is a highly classified operation--

808
00:54:21,280 --> 00:54:23,510
我授权第一夫人在场旁观行动
I'm clearing the First Lady for this operation.

809
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:25,520
好的  请原谅  先生
Yes, sir. Forgive me, sir.

810
00:54:25,520 --> 00:54:27,430
随时准备发射  先生
We are armed and ready, sir.

811
00:54:27,750 --> 00:54:29,760
阿卜杜拉就在那些车辆中
Abdullah is in one of those vehicles.

812
00:54:29,760 --> 00:54:31,050
具体哪一辆我们还不清楚
We can't tell which one.

813
00:54:31,050 --> 00:54:32,780
如果他们兵分三路行动的话
If they go in three different directions,

814
00:54:32,790 --> 00:54:33,960
我们将不知道该摧毁哪一路
we wouldn't know where to strike,

815
00:54:33,960 --> 00:54:35,800
如果让他逃回山中
and if he makes it back to the mountains,

816
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:37,760
我们的卫星就追踪不到他了
we'll lose our satellite track on him.

817
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:40,550
那些是孩子吗
Are those children?

818
00:54:40,720 --> 00:54:42,910
我不能确定  先生  但有这个可能
I can't say definitely, sir, but they could be.

819
00:54:45,660 --> 00:54:47,220
可以发动打击吗  先生
Do we have authorization, sir?

820
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:52,880
-行动吧  -执行打击
- Proceed. - Proceed with the launch.

821
00:54:55,050 --> 00:54:56,550
倒计时10秒
And ten seconds.

822
00:54:58,790 --> 00:55:03,950
And five, four, three...

823
00:55:14,070 --> 00:55:15,590
目标已摧毁  先生
Target is destroyed, sir.

824
00:55:18,530 --> 00:55:19,730
谢谢各位
Thank you, everyone.

825
00:55:43,090 --> 00:55:44,380
我还是要提名
I still want it.

826
00:55:47,850 --> 00:55:48,900
那好吧
All right.

827
00:55:52,560 --> 00:55:53,560
那好吧
All right.

828
00:56:12,910 --> 00:56:22,910
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}2011年夏天  美国总统奥巴马同国会就"债务上限"展开激烈争斗
在谈判中最终败给国会新当选的一批共和党保守派"茶党"的议员
共和党取得了谈判胜利
"债务上限"一役使奥巴马民望大跌  不仅反对派共和党对他不以为然
民主党内也有很多人认为他缺乏领导能力
为挽回民望和政治影响力
奥巴马于2011年9月8日在国会发表全国性讲话
郑重推出《美国工作法案》(American Jobs Act)
该法案拟在不增加预算赤字的情况下
通过不同渠道筹款四千四百七十亿美元  用于创造就业

829
00:56:37,910 --> 00:56:47,910
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}然而该法案推出后  不仅遭到国会共和党的强烈反对
在民主党占多数的参议院也没得到足够的支持
由于无法在国会得到通过  白宫被迫将这个法案分拆成几个小法案
但是即使委曲求全  分拆后的法案也大都没通过

